				 Tongue chopped
																								Mahoba, Oct. 6 (PTI): The tongue of a newly-wed woman was chopped off by her in-laws in an Uttar Pradesh village after her parents failed to meet their dowry demand, police said. 																								The woman, married six months ago, was allegedly given an injection by her in-laws before they cut her tongue off. She was later dumped in the nearby jungles. 																								The in-laws had been demanding a motorcycle and a gold chain.																								The victim has been admitted to Jhansi Medical College. 																								Her husband and his parents have been taken into custody, the police said.
